E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/2.html#T335b
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">335<SPAN CLASS="small">B</SPAN></A>, <I>infra</I>; T. Preger, <I>Inscriptiones Graecae


<A ID="p407x"></A><SPAN CLASS="pagenum">(p407)</SPAN>Metricae</I>, pp183‑187. The epigram is more completely given in the <I>Anthology</I>, <SPAN CLASS="small">XVI</SPAN>.120, where it is attributed to Archelaüs or Asclepiades. Probably, as Ouvré has seen, it belongs to the latter.


