<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note69" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref69
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">69</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/2.html#T338d
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">338<SPAN CLASS="small">D</SPAN></A>, <I>infra</I>;
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/6-7.html#47.7
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Life of Alexander</I>, chap. <SPAN CLASS="smaller">XLVII</SPAN> (691<SPAN CLASS="small">E</SPAN>)</A>; Arrian, <SPAN CLASS="small">IV</SPAN>.19;
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/8*.html#4
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Curtius, <SPAN CLASS="small">VIII</SPAN>.4</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note70" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref70
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">70</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/5.html#43.5
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><I>Life of Alexander</I>, chap. <SPAN CLASS="smaller">XLIII</SPAN> (690<SPAN CLASS="small">B</SPAN>)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note71" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref71
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">71</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <I>Moralia</I>, 180<SPAN CLASS="small">D</SPAN>, and the note.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note72" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref72
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">72</A>
<I>Cf.</I> Plato, <I>Symposium</I>, 218<SPAN CLASS="small">C</SPAN>;
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diogenes_Laertius/Lives_of_the_Eminent_Philosophers/2/Socrates*.html#31
	"TARGET="Diogenes_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Diogenes Laertius, <SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.31</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note73" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref73
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">73</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <I>Moralia</I>, 1099<SPAN CLASS="small">D</SPAN>;
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/3.html#22
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Life of Alexander</I>, chap. <SPAN CLASS="smaller">XXII</SPAN> (676<SPAN CLASS="small">F</SPAN>)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note74" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref74
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">74</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#T331e
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">331<SPAN CLASS="small">E</SPAN></A>, <I>supra</I>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note75" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref75
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">75</A>
Alexander's remark that he needed money to give to others may be compared to the remark which Plutarch quotes in his
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/8.html#60.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Life of Alexander</I>, chap. <SPAN CLASS="smaller">LX</SPAN> (698<SPAN CLASS="small">E</SPAN>)</A>, when Alexander was risking his life in crossing the swollen Hydaspes: "O Athens, can you possibly believe what dangers I undergo to win good repute among you?" Others think that the remark has been lost from the <SPAN CLASS="small">MSS.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note76" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref76
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">76</A>
Homer, <I>Il.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">XII</SPAN>.243 <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">εἷς οἰωνὸς ἄριστος ἀμύνεσθαι περὶ πάτρης</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note77" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref77
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">77</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/De_superstitione*.html#death_is_the_end_of_life
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Moralia</I>, 166<SPAN CLASS="small">F</SPAN></A>; Demosthenes, <I>De Corona</I>, 97. W. Crönert, in a review of Bell-Crum, <I>A Greek-Coptic Glossary</I> (<I>Gnomon</I>, <SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN> p657)<!-- https://www.jstor.org./stable/27673535 -->, reconstructs, from the works of


<A ID="p421x"></A><SPAN CLASS="pagenum">(p421)</SPAN>the Testament of the High Priest Fl. Phoebammon, trimeters of an Euripidean flavour:

<DIV ALIGN="center"><TABLE>
	<TR>
		<TD><DIV CLASS="verse"><SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">
πέρας δὲ παντὸς τοῦ βροτησίου γένους
			<BR>
ὁ θάνατός οὐδὲ δυνατόν ἐστιν ἐκφυγεῖν</SPAN>.
		</DIV></TD>
	</TR>
</TABLE></DIV>

	<P CLASS="halfstart justify">
More likely here, however, would be such a line as

<DIV ALIGN="center"><TABLE>
	<TR>
		<TD><DIV CLASS="verse"><SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">
ὁ θάνατός ἐσθ’ ἅπασιν ἀνθρώποις πέρας</SPAN>.
		</DIV></TD>
	</TR>
</TABLE></DIV>

	<P CLASS="halfstart justify">
Plutarch and Demosthenes may both be quoting from something of the sort.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note78" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/1.html#ref78
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">78</A>
	<A HREF="
https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Thuc.+2.87
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Thucydides,WIDTH,220)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Thucydides, <SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.87</A>.



